summary: I think maybe part of the reason people tend to hate on Dan more than Phil is because Phil is their “smol sunshine bean”...
question: I think maybe part of the reason people tend to hate on Dan more than Phil is because Phil is their “smol sunshine bean” (someone has said that exact thing I’m sure) and people feel like he’s pure or something and needs to be protected (regardless of the fact that he’s decades older than the majority of them)
answer: Yes, while I thankfully don’t see the “smol bean” talk as much as I used to, I agree that the phandom has created roles for Dan and Phil and see everything each of them does filtered through those glasses. While I do think Dan gets treated far more cruelly, this kind of thing does also speak very well to the infantalizing of Phil the phandom tend to do. There are definitely patterns of behavior established in the phandom for how Dan is treated and how Phil is treated that needed to be re-evaluated yesterday.

summary: my theory as to why people are so quick to bash dan is that they hold him responsible for him and phil "being in the closet" ......
question: my theory as to why people are so quick to bash dan is that they hold him responsible for him and phil "being in the closet" ... like 2012 is talked about as a horror story (written by dan himself) i've seen a lot of post talking about how toxic dan was for denying phan and saying that he and phil are just friends. there seems to be this collective head cannon, which is taken as fact, that he not only mistreated his "innocent" audience but also hurt phil. baically he's the scapegoat.
answer: I do think, as crazy as it sounds, you are onto something here. Even though the majority of the people in the phandom now probably had never even heard of Dan back in 2012, I see so many posts that say, “I wasn’t in the phandom in 2012, but it was awful, the worst year.” Unfortunately the people in this fandom who do the archiving are serious tinhatters who are committed to perpetuating the idea that Dan was “gaslighting” or “backtracking” or “acting homophobic,” because that supports their conspiracy theories, rather than presenting the more accurate story that he was a human being very upset by people like them invading his privacy, spreading rumors about him, and stalking him, his friend, and his family, who was pleading with people to try to understand where he was coming from and respect him. The really sad part is that people lashed out at him at the time because he was getting between them and their fantasies and wanted to punish him for it succeeded and, while most of them have probably moved on and don’t give “phan” a second thought, they pretty much slandered Dan and created this condescending and adversarial attitude that people still seem to have toward him today when he doesn’t act how they want him to. He’s still stuck dealing with the fallout half a decade later. Some of the language people were using after TTLMT was verbatim what people say when talking about “2012.” I don’t think Dan deserves any of it and I’m willing to die on that hill.
